cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR 

The paper deals with visual data and object recognition, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel approach towards learning an adaptive and common dictionary for multiple domains, which involves minimizing domain-shift among the data from each pair of domains. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions experiments on image classification, which suggests that it may belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a discriminative manifold regularization, which suggests that it may also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
